1. In Response Header set the header Cache-Control: max-age=0
2. In Response Header set the header Cache-Control: no-cache, this causes Page to load slow in some browsers
3. Server/origin/distribution setting can Adjust the TTLs
4 Change the name of the resourse(s) served like css, js, 
  html can be named their names appended with a incremental version number or current date/time stamp
5. In AWS certain paths can be invalidated but that is billable.
6. Cache Busting via Gulp or manual versioning(for resourse files like css, js or html)
7. Use [chunckhash] property in Webpack while creating the bundles for the app
